3E%3Cp%3EGriffith%20said%20there%20are%20several%20reasons%20someone%20may%20want%20to%20transfer%20their%20wealth%20early.%20For%20the%20very%20wealthy%2C%20that%20may%20be%20to%20avoid%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Festate-tax-homes-real-estate-wealthy-trusts-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elarge%20estate%20tax%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20even%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillionaire-age-millennials-inheriting-wealth-older-boomers-living-longer-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaverage%20baby%20boomers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20have%20a%20net%20worth%20of%20around%20%241%20million%2C%20are%20getting%20in%20on%20early%20wealth%20transfers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20want%20to%20share%2C%20and%20they%20want%20to%20witness%20wealth%20transfer%20while%20they're%20alive%20and%20healthy%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20main%20reason%20her%20clients%20want%20to%20share%20their%20wealth%20with%20their%20kids%20is%20%26quot%3Bjust%20because%20it%20makes%20them%20happy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGriffith%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Ffinancial-plan%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efinancial%20planning%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20especially%20important%20for%20parents%20who%20are%20thinking%20about%20sharing%20their%20wealth.%20In%20part%2C%20that's%20because%20many%20parents%20have%20a%20hard%20time%20saying%20%26quot%3Bno%26quot%3B%20if%20their%20child%20needs%20help%2C%20so%20it's%20best%20to%20work%20gifting%20into%20your%20financial%20plan%20from%20the%20start.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222f0d9dca-58ef-47e4-9e1b-337bcfcd9dff%5C%22%3EDo%20your%20finances%20pass%20a%20'stress%20test'%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGriffith%20said%20the%20first%20thing%20someone%20should%20do%20before%20transferring%20wealth%20is%20to%20look%20at%20their%20retirement%20resources%20and%20do%20something%20she%20calls%20a%20%26quot%3Bstress%20test.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20stress%20test%20is%20taking%20a%20look%20at%20the%20portfolio%20and%20modeling%20it%20in%20volatile%20markets%2C%20looking%20at%20the%20impact%20and%20actually%20the%20end%20results%20of%20their%20normal%20distribution%20to%20meet%20their%20needs%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThen%20adding%20in%20what%20I%20consider%20to%20be%20a%20goal%20distribution%2C%20something%20that%20is%20not%20paramount%20to%20living%2C%20but%20something%20that%20they%20really%2C%20really%20want%20to%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20includes%20considering%20what%20the%20portfolio%20might%20look%20like%20when%20the%20markets%20are%20most%20volatile%20and%20declining.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20portfolio%20can%20survive%20that%20and%20you%20still%20see%20that%20there%20are%20positive%20results%20at%20end%20of%20life%2C%20well%20now%20we%20can%20start%20to%20model%20in%20some%20type%20of%20a%20reasonable%20schedule%20to%20share%20some%20of%20the%20wealth%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20this%20strategy%2C%20Griffith%20said%20a%20parent%20can%20back%20into%20the%20number%20that%20they%20feel%20they%20are%20able%20to%20give%20to%20their%20kids.%20Although%20a%20parent%20might%20want%20to%20do%20the%20full%20tax-free%20gift%20amount%20(%2418%2C000%20for%20one%20person%20in%202024%2C%20%2436%2C000%20for%20a%20couple)%2C%20that%20might%20not%20be%20the%20right%20amount%20based%20on%20the%20resources%20they%20have%20when%20accounting%20for%20potential%20downturns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStress%20testing%20the%20portfolio%20is%20a%20way%20for%20them%20to%20make%20an%20informed%20decision%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bnot%20just%20with%20the%20heart%2C%20but%20also%20using%20the%20head%20so%20that%20they're%20also%20smart%20with%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGriffith%20said%20a%20wealth%20advisor%20can%20help%20complete%20a%20stress%20test%20using%20specific%20software%20that%20looks%20at%20various%20simulations%20of%20what%20could%20happen%20to%20a%20person's%20finances.%20For%20baby%20boomers%20who%20have%20a%20relationship%20with%20Citi%20and%20are%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffortune.com%2Frecommends%2Finvesting%2Fbaby-boomers-average-net-worth%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaverage%20net%20worth%20range%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20their%20generation%2C%20around%20%24970%2C000%20to%20%241.2%20million%20in%202019%2C%20she%20said%20financial%20planning%20is%20provided%20without%20extra%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20thing%20Griffith%20emphasized%20that%20is%20key%20for%20people%20to%20think%20about%20before%20gifting%20their%20wealth%20is%20end-of-life%20care.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnursing-home-private-room-monthly-median-price-by-state-2019-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENursing%20homes%20and%20assisted%20living%20facilities%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20easily%20cost%20%24100%2C000%20per%20year.%20As%20people%20are%20living%20longer%20than%20ever%2C%20some%20baby%20boomers%20could%20find%20themselves%20living%20in%20a%20care%20facility%20for%20not%20just%20for%20three%20or%20four%20years%20but%20up%20to%20a%20decade%20or%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20is%20one%20way%20to%20really%20start%20to%20deplete%20a%20portfolio%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20when%20stress%20testing%2C%20it's%20also%20important%20to%20model%20in%20what%20happens%20if%20someone's%20health%20declines%20and%20they%20need%20long-term%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGriffith%20said%20some%20of%20her%20favorite%20meetings%20with%20her%20clients%20are%20when%20someone%20comes%20in%20and%20says%20I%20want%20to%20gift%20this%20amount%20to%20my%20kids%2C%20or%20I%20want%20to%20help%20my%20kid%20make%20this%20large%20purchase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20excited%20to%20do%20it%20and%20so%20am%20I%20to%20be%20able%20to%20help%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20again%2C%20we%20want%20to%20make%