oughout%202018%20in%20order%20to%20hide%20hush%20money%20he%20paid%20to%20porn%20actor%20Stormy%20Daniels%20as%20part%20of%20a%20conspiracy%20to%20illegally%20influence%20the%202016%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20DA's%20filing%20is%20a%20response%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-now-says-scotus-immunity-voids-entire-hush-money-indictment-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eto%20defense%20arguments%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20prosecutorial%20immunity%20voids%20not%20just%20his%20conviction%2C%20but%20the%20hush-money%20indictment%20in%20its%20entirety.%20The%20SCOTUS%20decision%20found%20that%20using%20official-act%20evidence%20in%20prosecuting%20a%20current%20or%20former%20president%20violates%20their%20constitutional%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20defense%20argued%20the%20grand%20jurors%20who%20voted%20to%20indict%20Trump%20and%20the%20trial%20jurors%20who%20voted%20to%20convict%20him%20were%20all%20shown%20significant%20evidence%20involving%20Trump's%20official%20acts%2C%20and%20that%20this%20evidence%20is%20now%20retroactively%20inadmissible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20courtroom%20sketch%20of%20Donald%20Trump%20at%20his%20arraignment%2C%20with%20Manhattan%20District%20Attorney%20Alvin%20Bragg%20pictured%20seated%20behind%20him.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65c795876fcb546d2d4e4559%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221875%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDonald%20Trump%20at%20his%20arraignment%2C%20with%20Manhattan%20District%20Attorney%20Alvin%20Bragg%20seated%20behind%20him.%3Cp%3EReuters%2FJane%20Rosenberg%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Thursday%2C%20Bragg%20responded%20in%20papers%20signed%20by%20Matthew%20Colangelo%2C%20an%20assistant%20district%20attorney%20who%20was%20a%20lead%20prosecutor%20on%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20filing%20argues%20that%20Trump%20is%20wrong%20in%20now%20stamping%20much%20of%20the%20prosecutor's%20case%20%26quot%3Bofficial%20act%20evidence.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20defense%20is%20challenging%20four%20incriminating%202018%20tweets%20shown%20to%20jurors%20from%20Trump's%20personal%20Twitter%20account%2C%20in%20which%20he%20referred%20private%20payments%20to%20Daniels%20by%20his%20then-personal%20attorney%2C%20Michael%20Cohen.%20But%20these%20tweets%20describe%20unofficial%20acts%20unrelated%20to%20Trump's%20official%20duties%2C%20and%20for%20which%20he%20has%20no%20immunity%2C%20the%20prosecution%20filing%20now%20argues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTrump%20was%20not%20performing%2C%20or%20even%20describing%2C%20any%20official%20presidential%20act%20in%20conveying%20his%20personal%20opinions%20about%20his%20personal%20attorney%20and%20a%20private%20nondisclosure%20agreement%20entered%20into%20prior%20to%20his%20Presidency%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20filing%20says%20of%20the%20four%20tweets.%20%26quot%3BNo%20Presidential%20decision-making%20was%20involved.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20defense%20is%20also%20challenging%20trial%20testimony%20by%20Hope%20Hicks%2C%20Trump's%20former%20White%20House%20communications%20director%2C%20who%20described%20an%20incriminating%202018%20Oval%20Office%20conversation%20in%20which%20Trump%20expressed%20relief%20that%20Daniels'%20claims%20to%20a%20one-night%20sexual%20encounter%20surfaced%20only%20after%20the%202016%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20conversation%20again%20involved%20a%20hush-money%20scheme%20that%20%26quot%3Bwas%20entirely%20personal%20and%20largely%20committed%20before%20the%20election%2C%20and%20it%20had%20no%20relationship%20whatsoever%20to%20any%20official%20duty%20of%20the%20presidency%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20prosecution%20filing%20continues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditional%20challenged%20evidence%20%E2%80%94%20an%20incriminating%20government%20ethics%20form%20Trump%20signed%20in%202018%2C%20and%20snippets%20of%20trial%20testimony%20by%20Cohen%20and%20by%20Madeleine%20Westerhout%2C%20Trump's%20former%20White%20House%20assistant%20%E2%80%94%20all%20likewise%20concerned%20private%2C%20not%20presidential%2C%20matters%2C%20prosecutors%20argue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20if%20the%20challenged%20evidence%20was%20removed%20from%20the%20trial%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20error%20was%20harmless%20in%20light%20of%20the%20overwhelming%20evidence%20of%20defendant's%20guilt%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20filing%20argues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20tossing%20the%20underlying%20indictment%20%E2%80%94%20a%20move%20that%20would%20take%20Trump%20off%20the%20hook%20entirely%20%E2%80%94%20the%20prosecution%20filing%20argues%20that%20Trump%20would%20have%20been%20indicted%20even%20without%20what%20the%20defense%20calls%20%26quot%3Bofficial%20act%26quot%3B%20evidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20submission%20of%20some%20inadmissible%20evidence%20during%20the%20grand%20jury%20presentation%20%26quot%3Bis%20held%20to%20be%20fatal%20only%20when%20the%20remaining%20legal%20evidence%20is%20insufficient%20to%20sustain%20the%20indictment%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20filing%20says%2C%20quoting%20caselaw%20from%201996.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20indictment%20in%20this%20case%20was%20not%20'based%20on'%20any%20evidence%20of%20immune%20conduct%2C%26quot%3B%20prosecutors%20argue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELawyers%20for%20Trump%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20on%20the%20prosecution%20filing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20trial%20judge%2C%20state%20Supreme%20Court%20Justice%20Juan%20Merchan%2C%20has%20said%20he%20will%20issue%20a%20written%20decision%20on%20September%206%20on%20whether%20the%20indictment%20and%20conviction%20survive%20this%20challenge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20they%20do%2C%20Trump%20will%20be%20sentenced%20September%2018%20as%20planned%2C%20the%20judge%20has%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrumps-immunity-no-bearing-hush-money-conviction-da-bragg-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Inside