lone%20judge%20on%20the%20nine-judge%20constitution%20bench%20who%20did%20not%20concur%20with%20the%20majority%20verdict%20penned%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20DY%20Chandrachud%20which%20held%20that%20the%20legislative%20power%20to%20tax%20mineral%20rights%20vests%20with%20the%20states%20and%20the%20royalty%20paid%20on%20minerals%20is%20not%20a%20tax.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHolding%20a%20contrary%20view%2C%20Justice%20Nagarathna%2C%20in%20her%20193-page%20verdict%2C%20said%20royalty%20payable%20on%20minerals%20is%20in%20the%20nature%20of%20tax%20and%20not%20merely%20a%20contractual%20payment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20royalty%20is%20not%20held%20to%20be%20a%20tax%20and%20the%20same%20being%20covered%20under%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20MMDR%20Act%2C%201957%2C%20it%20would%20imply%20that%20despite%20Entry%2054-List%20I%20and%20the%20declaration%20made%20in%20section%202%20of%20the%20MMDR%20Act%2C%201957%E2%80%A6%2C%20taxes%20on%20mineral%20rights%20could%20be%20imposed%20by%20the%20States%20over%20and%20above%20payment%20of%20royalty%20on%20a%20holder%20of%20a%20mining%20lease%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEntry%2054%20of%20List%20I%20of%20the%20Constitution%20pertains%20to%20regulation%20of%20mines%20and%20mineral%20development%20by%20the%20Centre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20would%20be%20unhealthy%20competition%20between%20the%20States%20to%20derive%20additional%20revenue%20and%20consequently%2C%20the%20steep%2C%20uncoordinated%20and%20uneven%20increase%20in%20cost%20of%20minerals%20would%20result%20in%20the%20purchasers%20of%20such%20minerals%20coughing%20up%20huge%20monies%2C%20or%20even%20worse%2C%20would%20subject%20the%20national%20market%20being%20exploited%20for%20arbitrage%2C%26quot%3B%20Justice%20Nagarathna%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20the%20steep%20increase%20in%20prices%20of%20minerals%20would%20result%20in%20a%20hike%20in%20prices%20of%20all%20industrial%20and%20other%20products%20dependent%20on%20minerals%20as%20a%20raw%20material%20or%20for%20other%20infrastructural%20purposes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Nagarathna%20said%20as%20a%20result%2C%20the%20overall%20economy%20of%20India%20would%20be%20affected%20adversely%20which%20may%20result%20in%20certain%20entities%20or%20even%20non-extracting%20states%20importing%20minerals%20which%20would%20hamper%20foreign%20exchange%20reserves%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20would%20lead%20to%20a%20breakdown%20of%20the%20federal%20system%20envisaged%20under%20the%20Constitution%20in%20the%20context%20of%20mineral%20development%20and%20exercise%20of%20mineral%20rights.%20It%20could%20also%20lead%20to%20a%20slump%20in%20mining%20activity%20in%20States%20which%20have%20mineral%20deposits%20owing%20to%20huge%20levies%20that%20have%20to%20be%20met%20by%20holders%20of%20mining%20licences%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20another%20impact%20of%20this%20would%20be%20an%20%26quot%3Bunhealthy%20competition%26quot%3B%20to%20obtain%20mining%20leases%20in%20states%20which%20have%20mineral%20deposits%20and%20who%20do%20not%20wish%20to%20impose%20any%20other%20levy%20apart%20from%20royalty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%2C%20therefore%2C%20necessary%20to%20realise%20why%20the%20framers%20of%20the%20Constitution%20took%20a%20clue%20from%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20Act%2C%201935%20in%20order%20to%20distribute%20the%20legislative%20powers%20between%20the%20Union%20and%20the%20State%20List%20insofar%20as%20regulation%20of%20mines%20and%20minerals%20is%20concerned%2C%26quot%3B%20Justice%20Nagarathna%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReferring%20to%20future%20separate%20policy%20decisions%20to%20be%20taken%20by%20mineral-rich%20states%2C%20she%20said%20there%20might%20then%20be%20legal%20uncertainty%20which%20would%20cause%20adverse%20economic%20consequences%20including%20on%20mineral%20development%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20overruled%20a%202004%20verdict%20by%20a%20five-judge%20constitution%20bench%2C%20which%20while%20hearing%20a%20dispute%20over%20imposition%20of%20cess%20on%20land%20and%20mining%20activities%20between%20the%20state%20of%20West%20Bengal%20and%20Kesoram%20Industries%20Ltd%2C%20had%20held%20that%20royalty%20was%20not%20a%20tax.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Nagarathna%2C%20however%2C%20concurred%20with%20the%20CJI%20that%20the%20scope%20of%20the%20expression%20%26quot%3Bany%20limitations%26quot%3B%20under%20Entry%2050%20of%20List%20II%20is%20wide%20enough%20to%20include%20imposition%20of%20restriction%2C%20conditions%2C%20principles%20as%20well%20as%20a%20prohibition%20by%20Parliament%20by%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEntry%2050%20of%20List%20II%20pertains%20to%20taxes%20on%20mineral%20rights%20subject%20to%20any%20limitations%20imposed%20by%20Parliament%20by%20law%20relating%20to%20mineral%20development.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1721929260000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2Fc1l320oo_supreme-court-ani_625x300_23_February_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fthere-will-be-breakdown-of-federal-system-if-states-levy-taxes-on-minerals-justice-nagarathna-6187780%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20a%20dissenting%20verdict%2C%20Supreme%20Court%20judge%20Justice%20BV%20Nagarathna%20on%20Thursday%20said%20if%20the%20power%20to%20levy%20taxes%20on%20mineral%20resources%20are%20given%20to%20the%20states%2C%20there%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bbreakdown%20of%20the%20federal%20system%26quot%3B%20as%20they%20would%20compete%20among%20themselves.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fthere-will-be-breakdown-of-federal-system-if-states-levy-taxes-on-minerals-justice-nagarathna-6187780%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%2