ly%20badly%20made%20ones%20-%20are%20something%20nobody%20is%20willing%20to%20waste%20precious%20money%20and%20time%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Went%20Wrong%20With%20Bollywood%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETamil%2C%20Telugu%20and%20Malayalam%20films%20have%20been%20remade%20in%20Hindi%20consistently%20over%20the%20years%2C%20and%20now%2C%20Hollywood%20and%20Korean%20films%20are%20part%20of%20this%20mix%20too.%20But%20the%20audience%20seems%20to%20have%20reached%20a%20point%20of%20fatigue.%20With%20the%20rise%20of%20OTT%2C%20original%20content%20is%20easily%20available%20online%20-%20and%20this%20is%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20factors%20why%20many%20remakes%20don't%20work%20any%20more.%20Post-Covid-19%2C%20global%20content%20has%20become%20available%20to%20viewers%20readily%2C%20and%20at%20a%20fraction%20of%20the%20money%20a%20person%20usually%20spends%20watching%20a%20film%20in%20theatres.%20By%20the%20time%20a%20remake%20comes%20out%2C%20most%20have%20either%20already%20watched%20the%20original%20work%20online%2C%20or%20the%20thrill%20of%20seeing%20the%20film%20wanes.%20To%20add%20to%20that%2C%20if%20the%20remake%20is%20bad%2C%20it%20bombs%20all%20the%20more%20heavily%20at%20the%20box%20office.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Ffrom-maidaan-to-chandu-champion-how-bollywoods-obsession-with-big-budget-films-has-cost-it-dearly-6075493%5C%22%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%C2%A0It's%20Time%20Bollywood%20Gave%20Small-Budget%20Films%20The%20Respect%20They%20Deserve%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20string%20of%20recent%20flops%20begs%20the%20question%2C%20what's%20stopping%20the%20Hindi%20film%20industry%20from%20focusing%20on%20original%20content%2C%20and%20why%20is%20it%20instead%20choosing%20to%20rely%20on%20stale%20concepts%3F%20The%20plethora%20of%20successful%20web%20series%20on%20streaming%20platforms%20has%20already%20shown%20that%20there%20is%20no%20dearth%20of%20good%20writers%20in%20the%20Hindi%20film%20industry.%20Why%20then%20producers%20willing%20to%20bet%20on%20original%20content%20are%20few%20and%20far%20between%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20theatrical%20space%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBet%20On%20Original%20Content%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndigenous%20stories%20and%20stories%20that%20are%20culturally%20rooted%20have%20always%20resonated%20with%20Indian%20audiences%2C%20and%20that%20is%20evident%20right%20from%20a%20blockbuster%20like%20%3Cem%3ERRR%20%3C%2Fem%3Eto%20smaller%20movies%20like%20%3Cem%3EMunjya%3C%2Fem%3E.%20%3Cem%3EKalki%202898%20AD%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20sci-fi%20film%20based%20on%20the%20Mahabharata%2C%20was%20a%20hit%2C%20and%20so%20was%20the%20relatively%20low-scale%20%3Cem%3EHanu-Man%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20based%20on%20the%20Hindu%20God%2C%20Hanuman.%20Both%20films%20come%20from%20the%20Telugu%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Hindi%20film%20industry%20is%20the%20largest%20film%20industry%20in%20India%2C%20and%20yet%2C%20it%20continues%20to%20suffer%20from%20an%20identity%20crisis%2C%20which%20has%20only%20worsened%20over%20the%20last%20decade%20or%20two.%20From%20creating%20original%20content%2C%20the%20Hindi%20film%20industry%20moved%20to%20Westernisation%20of%20Hindi%20plots%2C%20and%20then%20remakes.%20It%20lost%20its%20USP%20in%20this%20process.%C2%A0In%20December%202022%2C%20Bollywood%20filmmaker%20Karan%20Johar%20said%20in%20an%20interview%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20core%20issue%20is%20that%20we%20come%20from%20a%20mainstream%20industry%20in%20Hindi%20cinema%2C%20and%20that%20includes%20myself%2C%20which%20does%20not%20have%20one%20very%20strong%20quality%20that%20every%20other%20cinema%20on%20this%20panel%20has.%20That%20is%20conviction.%20We%20kind%20of%20always%20go%20with%20the%20flow.%20We%20had%20such%20an%20original%20voice%20in%20Salim-Javed%20in%20the%2070s.%20We%20created%20a%20certain%20character%20and%20the%20concept%20of%20that%20angsty%2C%20angry%20hero%20was%20derived%20from%20other%20cinemas.%20Then%2C%20in%20the%2080s%2C%20suddenly%20something%20happened%20and%20there%20came%20a%20host%20of%20remakes.%20That's%20where%20the%20conviction%20loss%20started.%20We%20started%20remaking%20every%20film%20popular%20in%20Tamil%20and%20Telugu.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EConviction%20And%20Spine%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBollywood%20continues%20to%20produce%20some%20of%20the%20best%20films%20in%20India%2C%20but%20these%20are%20not%20enough%20to%20keep%20the%20industry%20thriving.%20Trade%20pundits%20say%20it's%20a%20matter%20of%20demand%20and%20supply%2C%20and%20with%20umpteen%20options%20before%20them%2C%20viewers%20are%20now%20demanding%20quality%2C%20original%20content%20that%20is%20entertaining%20as%20well.%C2%A0Given%20the%20multifront%20competition%20Bollywood%20today%20faces%20from%20regional%20cinema%20and%20Hollywood%20alike%2C%20filmmakers%20in%20B-Town%20must%20start%20putting%20their%20money%20into%20original%20stories%20if%20they%20want%20to%20strike%20gold%20at%20the%20box%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20actually%20lack%20-%20and%20I%20say%20this%20more%20for%20myself%20than%20anyone%20else%20-%20we%20lack%20the%20spine%20and%20conviction.%20That's%20what%20we%20need%20to%20get%20from%20all%20the%20other%20industries%2C%26quot%3B%20Johar%20said%20in%20the%20same%20interview.%20The%20time%20to%20acknowledge%20that%20is%20now.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(The%20author%20is%20a%20senior%20entertainment%20journalist%20and%20film%20critic)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1721913840000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-07%2Fb1idukr8_remakes_625x300_25_July_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fsarfira-to-shehzada-bollywoods-obsession-with-remakes-is-destroying-it-6187138%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%