s%20to%20humans%20through%20droplets%20from%20the%20urine%2C%20saliva%2C%20or%20faeces%20of%20the%20rats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20January%20to%20July%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fein.az.gov%2Femergency-information%2Femergency-bulletin%2Fincrease-hantavirus-activity-two-deaths-reported-coconino%5C%22%3EArizona%20Department%20of%20Health%20Services%3C%2Fa%3E%20documented%20seven%20instances%20of%20Hantavirus%20Pulmonary%20Syndrome%2C%20a%20serious%20and%20occasionally%20lethal%20respiratory%20disease.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20cases%20related%20to%20this%20deadly%20virus%20have%20also%20been%20found%20in%20California.%20The%20virus%2C%20primarily%20carried%20by%20deer%20mice%20in%20the%20Grand%20Canyon%20State%2C%20causes%20symptoms%20such%20as%20fever%2C%20headache%2C%20and%20muscle%20pain%2C%20which%20can%20rapidly%20progress%20to%20difficulty%20breathing.%20While%20hantavirus%20is%20not%20spread%20from%20person%20to%20person%2C%20it%20can%20occur%20in%20various%20regions%20and%20is%20not%20limited%20to%20a%20specific%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fhantavirus%2Fabout%2Findex.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DHantaviruses%2520can%2520infect%2520and%2520cause%2Crodent%252C%2520but%2520this%2520is%2520rare.%5C%22%3EUS%20Centres%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention%20(CDC)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20hantaviruses%20are%20a%20family%20of%20viruses%20spread%20mainly%20by%20rodents%20and%20can%20cause%20varied%20disease%20syndromes%20in%20people%20worldwide.%20This%20can%20cause%20hantavirus%20pulmonary%20syndrome%20(HPS)%20and%20hemorrhagic%20fever%20with%20renal%20syndrome%20(HFRS)%2C%20the%20CDC%20website%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESymptoms%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHantavirus%20symptoms%20start%20with%20fatigue%2C%20fever%2C%20muscle%20aches%2C%20headaches%2C%20chills%2C%20nausea%2C%20vomiting%2C%20and%20abdominal%20pain.%20Late%20symptoms%20include%20coughing%20and%20shortness%20of%20breath%2C%20with%20a%2038%25%20mortality%20rate%20for%20hantavirus%20pulmonary%20syndrome.%20Hemorrhagic%20fever%20with%20renal%20syndrome%20(HFRS)%20symptoms%20appear%201-8%20weeks%20post-exposure%2C%20causing%20headaches%2C%20pain%2C%20fever%2C%20chills%2C%20nausea%2C%20and%20blurred%20vision.%20Severe%20cases%20may%20lead%20to%20low%20blood%20pressure%2C%20shock%2C%20vascular%20leakage%2C%20and%20kidney%20failure.%20Recovery%20can%20take%20weeks%20or%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETreatment%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CDC%20says%20there%20is%20no%20specific%20treatment%2C%20cure%2C%20or%20vaccine%20for%20hantavirus%20infection.%20However%2C%20if%20the%20infected%20are%20recognised%20early%20on%20and%20are%20provided%20medical%20care%20in%20an%20intensive%20care%20unit%2C%20they%20may%20do%20better.%20In%20intensive%20care%2C%20patients%20are%20intubated%20and%20given%20oxygen%20therapy%20to%20help%20them%20through%20the%20period%20of%20severe%20respiratory%20distress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPrevention%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Centres%20for%20Disease%20Control%2C%20rodent%20control%20is%20the%20primary%20necessity%20to%20prevent%20hantavirus%20infections.%20Contact%20with%20rodent%20urine%2C%20droppings%2C%20saliva%2C%20and%20nesting%20materials%20should%20be%20avoided%20when%20cleaning%20rodent-infested%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1721911260000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-07%2Fb4tt4ibo_rat_625x300_25_July_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fhantavirus-death-in-us-deadly-rat-disease-spreads-to-humans-kills-4-in-us-6186912%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Hantavirus%3A%20According%20to%20the%20US%20Centres%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention%2C%20this%20virus%20is%20a%20family%20of%20viruses%20spread%20mainly%20by%20rodents%20and%20can%20cause%20varied%20disease%20syndromes.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22e